Package org.svvrl.goal.cmd

Interface Summary
CommandExtension This interface is used to extend the commands of GOAL.
ComplementConstructionInterface This interface is used to extend the complementation constructions available in ComplementExtension.
Expression An Expression provides an interface of expressions in GOAL scripts.
GameSolverInterface This interface defines a command-line plugin for game solvers.
Statement A statement is a block of expressions containing control flows.

AccCommand This command provides maximization and minimization of Büchi acceptance conditions of finite state automata.
AlphabetCommand This class provides a command that can manipulate the alphabet of an automaton.
AperiodicCommand An aperiodic command can test the aperiodicity of an automaton or the language of an automaton.
BatchCommand A batch command can execute a GOAL script.

ComplementExpression This class provides a command for taking the complement of an automaton.
ComplementExpression.ComplementTask

Constant A constant is an object that can be evaluated without the context.

ContinueStmt A ContinueStmt can continue a for-loop or a while-loop.

ForStmt A for-loop statement binds an element in a set of objects to a lvalue in one iteration and executes its body statement iteratively for every binding.

IfStmt An if-statement contains a set of guarded branches.

NullExpr A NullExpr is evaluated to null always.

PlusPlus This class provides expressions of the form ++$x or $x++ where $x is an l-value.
